  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stabilisation and economic recovery project in Timbuktu, Mopti and Segou (Project REGAL)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Communities in Timbuktu, Mopti and Segou</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This consortium project (including alert, Living eart Foundation, AMSS and ARGA) works across six communes in Timbuktu to address reconciliation, economic recovery and governance issues that contribute to post conflict instability.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to address the underlying causal factors of Mali?s recent crisis, which if not addressed, will continue to fuel instability and a recurrence of the current conflict.
The project will address three pillars of post-conflict stability and development: reconciliation, economic recovery and governance. Supporting positive, concrete examples of reconciliation and restorative justice, that show tangible impacts at the local level, will build upon the momentum of social cohesion in the region, and strengthen the social bonds across communities. Greater understanding of the dynamics of trade ? both formal and informal, legal and illicit ? and the changes that have taken place during the crisis (migration, loss of savings, disruption of education, etc.) in the region will be used to inform targeting and design of pilot projects in order to reinforce not only economic outcomes, but also social benefits. Equally, inclusion of both existing and emerging leadership structures in the reconciliation and reconstruction process will contribute to addressing root causes of conflict and redefine consensus politics that has hampered decentralisation at local levels in Mali.</narrative>
  </description>
